value.title: Federal prosecutors came to suspect Trump Org CFO Allen Weisselberg lied
value.excerpt: New York federal prosecutors came to suspect the Trump Organization's chief financial officer, Allen Weisselberg, lied in testimony during their investigation of former Trump personal attorney Michael Cohen three years ago, according to four people familiar with prosecutors' thinking.

value.title: Biden on Cuomo's resignation: 'I respect the governor's decision'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said Tuesday that he respects New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo's decision to resign after the President called on Cuomo to step down last week following an official report that said Cuomo sexually harassed multiple women.

value.title: Biden: $1 trillion infrastructure bill ‘will transform America’
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden called the $1 trillion infrastructure bill “historic” and said that it will “transform America.” The bill will make a huge investment in nation’s roads, public transit, water and broadband.

value.title: Trump's acting attorney general revealed 'frightening' activity at Justice Department, Senate Judiciary chair says
value.excerpt: Senate Judiciary Chairman Dick Durbin said Sunday that former acting Attorney General Jeffrey Rosen revealed in testimony this weekend "frightening" information about what had occurred at the Justice Department during the waning days of the Trump administration.

value.title: Bidens to meet virtually with Team USA athletes
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and first lady Jill Biden will meet with members of the 2020 US Olympic Team Saturday in a livestreamed virtual reception.

value.title: Fact-checking claim Biden administration is pushing vaccine passport
value.excerpt: Amid confusion over mask mandates, booster shots, and new guidance for those vaccinated, some Republicans have thrown fuel on the fire with false and misleading claims.

value.title: 9/11 families tell Biden to stay away from memorial service if he doesn't authorize release of records related to attacks
value.excerpt: More than 1,600 people affected by the September 11 attacks are asking President Joe Biden to refrain from coming to Ground Zero to mark the 20th anniversary of the event unless he releases documents and information related to the attacks, according to a letter released by the group.

value.title: The Point: You shouldn't miss this massive bombshell in Trump's ongoing election fraud lie
value.excerpt: Unless you have been living on another planet for the past six months, you know by now that Donald Trump leaned on state and national officials in the final days of his presidency to force investigations into made-up claims of widespread election fraud in the 2020 race.

value.title: Biden to announce new emissions standards, target that 50% of vehicles sold in US by 2030 are electric
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden will sign an executive order Thursday that points the US auto market toward electric vehicles, announcing a new target that half of vehicles sold in the country by 2030 will be battery electric, fuel-cell electric or plug-in hybrid.

value.title: White House cyber official says 'commitment' by ransomware gang suggests Biden's warnings are working
value.excerpt: White House Deputy National Security Advisor Anne Neuberger said Wednesday that the Biden administration thinks recent comments by a representative of a ransomware gang linked to the May attack on the Colonial Pipeline could amount to a "commitment" the group would not target critical infrastructure

value.title: 'If you aren't going to help, please get out of the way': Biden turns up the pressure on GOP governors as Delta spreads
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Tuesday will provide an update on his administration's Covid-19 vaccination efforts as the highly contagious Delta variant rips across the country, a White House official tells CNN.

value.title: Clinton. Trump. Cuomo. Powerful men in politics are often rewarded.
value.excerpt: The most powerful men in politics. They're often rewarded for having no shame.

value.title: Mike Carey, endorsed by Trump, will win Ohio GOP special primary, CNN projects
value.excerpt: Mike Carey, a coal lobbyist who was endorsed by former President Donald Trump, will win the Republican special primary in Ohio's 15th Congressional District, CNN projects.

value.title: Harris to promote 'America is back' message in Singapore and Vietnam
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris is set to travel to Singapore and Vietnam later this month, becoming the highest-ranking Biden administration official to visit Asia so far.

value.title: White House once again makes Covid-19 the focus of Biden's schedule
value.excerpt: The White House is making a concerted effort to return the focus of President Joe Biden's schedule to Covid-19 this week as the year-and-a-half-long pandemic again consumes his agenda amid a new spike in cases.

value.title: Mark Meadows: Trump meeting with his 'cabinet' (despite not having one)
value.excerpt: Former Trump White House Chief of Staff Mark Meadows told Newsmax that the former president has been holding meetings with his "cabinet" despite not being president. New York Times reporter and CNN political analyst Maggie Haberman has the details.

value.title: Delta, Trump, Haiti: Your Friday Evening Briefing
value.excerpt: The rare Friday session comes as Senate Democrats race to pass the bipartisan bill before leaving for the August recess. The emerging deal will provide $550 billion in new funding,but it still faces a bumpy road.

value.title: Justice Department advises Biden administration to hand over Trump tax returns to Congress
value.excerpt: The Justice Department told the Treasury Department that it "must" turn over former President Donald Trump's tax returns to the House Ways and Means Committee, which first requested them more than two years ago.

value.title: Trump to DOJ last December: 'Just say that the election was corrupt + leave the rest to me'
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump pressured his incoming acting Attorney General Jeffrey Rosen to declare that the election was corrupt in an attempt to help Republican members of Congress try to overturn the election result, according to notes of a December 2020 call Trump held with Rosen and acting deputy

value.title: Biden says Western wildfires demand 'urgent action' in meeting with governors
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said Friday the wildfires intensifying in the West demand "urgent action" as he met with seven governors to discuss how states are responding to the wildfires and how the federal government can best assist.

value.title: Biden to accept award from Kosovo on behalf of his son Beau
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Sunday will accept an award from the President of Kosovo on behalf of his son Beau Biden for his work helping to strengthen the war-torn country's justice system, according to a White House official.

value.title: Biden shifts onus for pandemic onto the unvaccinated as he readies federal worker vaccine requirement
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden, who for months used techniques like public service announcements and grassroots campaigns to persuade Americans to get vaccinated, is adopting a tougher approach as caseloads surge: vaccine requirements and blame.

value.title: Trump's inroads with Florida Latinos are influencing Democratic response to Cuba
value.excerpt: Democrats in South Florida, beleaguered by a tough 2020 election in the state, have been privately and publicly urging their party leaders to embrace the protests against Cuba's communist regime that are roiling the island nation.

value.title: Plan to honor Trump with banquet becomes flashpoint at one of America's most elite golf clubs
value.excerpt: The former president has been a member of Winged Foot, one of the country's top golf clubs and host of the 2020 U.S. Open, for more than 50 years.

value.title: McAuliffe attacks Youngkin by tying him to Trump's election lies
value.excerpt: Virginia's Terry McAuliffe, in an effort to tie his gubernatorial opponent, Glenn Youngkin, to all things Donald Trump, is now linking the Republican nominee to the former President's top focus: so-called election integrity.

value.title: US, Russia hold 'substantive' strategic stability talks as Moscow raps Biden for comments
value.excerpt: US and Russian officials had "professional and substantive talks" on strategic stability in Switzerland, the State Department said in a statement Wednesday.

value.title: Trump snubs Bush by endorsing Paxton in Texas AG race
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump has endorsed Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton in his bid for re-election, snubbing George P. Bush despite his firm support after Trump has belittled some members of the Bush family.

value.title: January 6 committee opening is crucial chance to correct Trump's lies
value.excerpt: The tasks before the Democratic-led House Select Committee examining the January 6 insurrection that opens on Tuesday, after bitter partisan feuding over its make-up, could hardly be more critical.

value.title: Trump ally Tom Barrack pleads not guilty in foreign lobbying case
value.excerpt: Tom Barrack, a longtime ally of former President Donald Trump and chairman of the Trump 2016 Inaugural Committee, pleaded not guilty through his attorney on Monday to illegal foreign lobbying charges unveiled by the Justice Department last week.

value.title: Biden jumps backs into campaigning with McAuliffe rally in Virginia
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is making his return to the campaign trail.
